 :schema-version "1.0"
 :scenario-title "Freeze recovery — rotate then slash then unfreeze then new escrow with same resolver"
 :scenario-author "@kilo-research"
 :scenario-id "s-dr-089-freeze-recovery"
 :scenario-purpose "Demonstrate the correct freeze-recovery sequence: rotate-dispute-resolver to reassign the active dispute away from resolver1 BEFORE proposing/executing the fraud slash. This avoids the resolver-not-frozen-on-assign invariant violation shown in DR-M-003. After unfreeze, the same resolver can accept new escrows."
